+/*
+ * SYS_IMP_APL_CYC_OVRD = s3_5_c15_c5_0
+ * SYS_IMP_APL_ACC_OVRD = s3_5_c15_c6_0
+ *
+ * CYC_OVRD bits:
+ *   [25:24] WFI_MODE: 0=normal, 3=deep WFI (cluster power-down capable)
+ *   [0]     DISABLE_WFI_RET: disable WFI return (stay in deep WFI)
+ *
+ * ACC_OVRD bits (from m1-deepsleep research on T8103):
+ *   [18:17] TRAIN_DOWN_LINK: 3=train-down interconnect on idle (saves power)
+ *   [26:25] POWER_DOWN_CPM:  3=power-down cluster PM unit on idle
+ *   [32]    DISABLE_PIO:     disable PIO on WFI (reduce leakage)
+ *
+ * The stock Asahi driver only sets CYC_OVRD WFI_MODE=3. Adding ACC_OVRD
+ * tuning enables deeper cluster-level power gating without requiring
+ * cold reset (unlike DEEP_SLEEP bit 34 which is too aggressive for idle).
+ */
